olive oil
1 packet gnocchi
1 packet pulled chicken
½ packet cream
1 packet garlic paste
1 cup water
2 radish
1 bag Deluxe Salad Mix
1 bag parsley
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Place gnocchi in a baking dish.
• Drizzle with olive oil (2 tbs for 2 people / 1/4 cup for 4 people).
• Season, toss to coat and spread out evenly. Bake until golden, 10-14 minutes.

• Remove gnocchi from the oven, then add pulled chicken, breaking up with a spoon. • Stir in Aussie spice blend, garlic paste, grated Parmesan cheese, cream (see ingredients) and the water.
• Return to the oven, then bake until sauce has reduced, 10-12 minutes. Season to taste.
• Meanwhile, thinly slice radish.
• In a large bowl, combine deluxe salad mix, radish and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide creamy pulled chicken and gnocchi bake between bowls.
• Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Tear over parsley to garnish.
• Serve with radish salad. Enjoy!